params.html:
Health Coaching 101

Your free guide to everything you need to know about health coaching and the benefits of becoming a Health Coach.

form_field.message: Thank you for your interest! Please look for an email message from us in your inbox shortly and an Admission Coaching to reach out soon.

params.html: By submitting the form, I consent to Integrative Nutrition and its affiliates contacting me by email at the address provided and/or by telephone at the number provided (by live, automated, or prerecorded phone calls or text messages) about its courses. I understand that my consent is not required for enrollment and may be withdrawn. This page is protected by Google reCAPTCHA.
The IIN Approach to Health, Wellness, and Health Coaching

The world is experiencing a healthcare crisiswe have unlimited access to health information, but we've never been sicker...

  • Worldwide obesity has nearly tripled in the last 50 years.
  • Chronic diseases are currently projected to account for almost three-quarters of all deaths worldwide, such as heart disease, stroke, and diabetes.
  • 6 in 10 Americans live with at least one chronic disease.
  • Obesity impacts 1 in 5 children and 1 in 3 adults in the U.S., costing the healthcare system $147 billion each year.

Millions of people around the world need guidanceneed your guidanceto make diet and lifestyle changes to reverse these trends and transform their health and wellbeing. Health Coaches are trained to become part of the greater health care team, working alongside doctors, physicians, and other wellness professionals to provide people with the integrated care they need to live a healthy lifestyle.

IIN is home to the worlds leading health coaching certification program, The Health Coach Training Program. Founded over 30 years ago, our community has over 160,000 coaches in over 175 countries, all working to help others live their healthiest, happiest lives.

We're the most reputable and long-standing educational institution that will prepare you to not only reach these people in need, but help them meet their health goals, transform their lives to achieve long-term health, and in the process, transform yours.

IIN takes a holistic, no-one-size-fits-all approach to nutrition and wellness.

You'll explore more than 100 dietary theories such as plant-based eating, Ayurveda, and raw foods, plus learn the life-coaching and behavior-change skills needed to become a successful Health Coach, empowering clients in your coaching sessions to reach their health goals.

We'll teach you that achieving optimal health is not just about the food on your plate.

It's also about how you nourish yourself through your relationships, spirituality, career, environment, and much more. This is the true IIN difference, giving you the confidence you need to go out into the world and change lives. Whatever your professional interests or personal goals, get an unparalleled education that will transform the health and lives of others, as well as your own.

The future looks bright! Thank you for submitting your request to book an exclusive 1-1 consultation.

We cant wait to meet you! A program expert will be in touch within 1 business day. You will also receive confirmation of this request in your email inbox. In the meantime, we encourage you to explore our health and wellness resources.
Upcoming Live & Free Webinars

Your Roadmap to NBHWC Certification: A Live Q&A Session

{% icon icon_set="fontawesome-6.4.2" name="Clock" style="SOLID" height="14" purpose="decorative" title="Clock icon" %} June 25, 2024 at 1:00pm ET

In this LIVE Q&A about board certification through the NBHWC (National Board for Health and Wellness Coaching), youll join IIN graduates and admission representatives to learn more about how becoming NBHWC board-certified validates your expertise as a health coach, enhances your credibility with clients, and opens up more professional opportunities.
Register Now

Instant Zen: Unlocking the Power of Yoga

{% icon icon_set="fontawesome-6.4.2" name="Clock" style="SOLID" height="14" purpose="decorative" title="Clock icon" %} May 23, 2024 at 12:00pm ET

May is Mental Health Awareness Month, and mindfulness is top of mind. Come join an immersive session focused on incorporating mindfulness into your daily life through the practice of yoga. Led by Sarah Platt-Finger, the Director of Chopra Yoga at IIN, this session will include mindfulness tools that you can use throughout your day. You will also hear from Chopra Yoga graduates, who will explain how yoga has helped them live a more mindful and purposeful life, and how the Chopra Yoga 200-Hour Teacher Training program changed their lives.
Register Now

Create Content That Converts With IINBiz  

{% icon icon_set="fontawesome-6.4.2" name="Clock" style="SOLID" height="14" purpose="decorative" title="Clock icon" %} May 15, 2024 at 2pm ET

Are you looking to grow your wellness business, but dont know how to market it? Join us for a live conversation to learn how IINBiz can help! IINBiz has all the marketing tools you need to launch and manage your business, including ready-to-use web and social media content, webinar scripts, email newsletters, and more. Learn how to grow your business without taking time away from doing the work you love.
Register Now
Explore Upcoming Live & Free Webinars

Live Health Coaching Open House: Your Roadmap to a Fulfilling Life and Career

{% icon icon_set="fontawesome-6.4.2" name="Clock" style="SOLID" height="14" purpose="decorative" title="Clock icon" %} July 10, 2024 at 1:00pm ET

This live workshop is geared to help you understand why enrolling with IIN is a unique and impactful experience. Youll discover how a health coaching certification can elevate your life, health, and career, and how you can take your coaching to the next level by becoming board certified with the National Board for Health & Wellness Coaching (NBHWC). The Health Coach Training Program starts on July 22nd, so this is the perfect opportunity to learn more before you enroll. Plus, youll unlock special tuition savings!
Register Now

Empower Your Hormone Health at Any Stage of Life

{% icon icon_set="fontawesome-6.4.2" name="Clock" style="SOLID" height="14" purpose="decorative" title="Clock icon" %} July 16, 2024 at 1:00pm ET

Join us at our free Open House and learn why caring for your hormones is an important lifelong endeavor. Its never too late or too early to make diet and lifestyle shifts that will support your hormones at any stage of life, including pregnancy, perimenopause, and menopause. If youre a coach focusing on a hormone health niche, you wont want to miss this deep dive into the hottest topics in hormone health today!
Register Now

Ayurveda for Gut Health: In Conversation with Dr. Tom OBryan and Dr. Sheila Patel

{% icon icon_set="fontawesome-6.4.2" name="Clock" style="SOLID" height="14" purpose="decorative" title="Clock icon" %} May 22, 2024 at 1:30pm ET

Discover how the ancient wisdom of Ayurveda can be applied to the modern day in this immersive webinar featuring Dr. Tom OBryan and Dr. Sheila Patel, two renowned experts and IIN faculty members. Gut health isnt just a buzzword its a key area of health. And when your gut is imbalanced and inflamed, it can wreak havoc on the rest of your body. Learn how to take control of your gut health and implement holistic tools to support and optimize your well-being!

params.html: We're so happy Stef Jung shared her love of IIN's Mindful Eating Course with you!

params.html:
Why apply for the Stef Jung Mindful Eating Scholarship? 

Stef Jungs relationship with food and her body from dieting to emotional eating to binge eating controlled her life. But now she has a nourishing, balanced, loving relationship with whats on her plate, and shes turned her mess into her message to help others improve their relationship with food.  

This is the course I wish I had at the time. Im so excited to not only be a guest lecturer for IINs Mindful Eating Course, but also to be able to give it to one lucky winner. This course takes the confusion and guesswork out of the process and provides you with all the tools and guidance you need to ditch diet culture, unleash your inner food wisdom, and become an intuitive eater. 

 

Stef Jung, IIN Grad, Intuitive Eating Holistic Health Coach, Guest Lecturer in IIN's Mindful Eating Course 

The Stef Jung Mindful Eating Scholarship is geared towards those who want to learn how to honor their bodys unique physical and emotional needs. I understand that my consent is not required for enrollment and may be withdrawn. This page is protected by Google reCAPTCHA.
Benefits of the Mindful Eating Course

Formerly called the Emotional Eating Course, the new and improved Mindful Eating Course will teach you how to find nourishment on and off your plate, and it will empower you to create practices that improve your relationship with food. Throughout the course, well dive deep into:

params.text:
The Mindful Eating Process:
Youll enhance mindfulness around your food-related behaviors, biology, and beliefs through self-awareness practices, self-compassion, and an exploration of your own food narrative.

Root Causes and Triggers of Emotional Eating:
From stress and lack of sleep to body ideals and diet culture, well deconstruct common biases and norms that fuel unhelpful habits. Plus, youll develop a deeper understanding of your relationship with food.

Nourishment Beyond Food:
Well encourage you to create a more vibrant life through self-healing tools found off your plate, including relationships, self-care, and more. A well-rounded you is a more balanced you!

The IIN Approach to Health, Wellness, and Health Coaching

The world is experiencing a healthcare crisiswe have unlimited access to health information, but we've never been sicker...

  • Worldwide obesity has nearly tripled in the last 50 years.
  • Chronic diseases are currently projected to account for almost three-quarters of all deaths worldwide, such as heart disease, stroke, and diabetes.
  • 6 in 10 Americans live with at least one chronic disease.
  • Obesity impacts 1 in 5 children and 1 in 3 adults in the U.S., costing the healthcare system $147 billion each year.

Millions of people around the world need guidanceneed your guidanceto make diet and lifestyle changes to reverse these trends and transform their health and wellbeing. Health Coaches are trained to become part of the greater health care team, working alongside doctors, physicians, and other wellness professionals to provide people with the integrated care they need to live a healthy lifestyle.

IIN is home to the worlds leading health coaching certification program, The Health Coach Training Program. Founded over 30 years ago, our community has over 160,000 coaches in over 175 countries, all working to help others live their healthiest, happiest lives.

We're the most reputable and long-standing educational institution that will prepare you to not only reach these people in need, but help them meet their health goals, transform their lives to achieve long-term health, and in the process, transform yours.

IIN takes a holistic, no-one-size-fits-all approach to nutrition and wellness.

You'll explore more than 100 dietary theories such as plant-based eating, Ayurveda, and raw foods, plus learn the life-coaching and behavior-change skills needed to become a successful Health Coach, empowering clients in your coaching sessions to reach their health goals.

We'll teach you that achieving optimal health is not just about the food on your plate.

It's also about how you nourish yourself through your relationships, spirituality, career, environment, and much more. This is the true IIN difference, giving you the confidence you need to go out into the world and change lives. Whatever your professional interests or personal goals, get an unparalleled education that will transform the health and lives of others, as well as your own.
